																			as cheap and tacky or expensive and elegant.</p>

																		<p>Subtle touches such as careful alignment and spacing, the use of bullet points and ornamental separations between paragraphs are just some of the things that individually may not sound like much but together add up to create a stunning layout that
																			you would expect from a Royal wedding.</p>


																		<p>Stuff from Lidl looks and feels cheaper than the premium products at Waitrose. </p>

																			<h6 style="width:50%;font-size:18pt;margin-top:1em;">The Sun newspaper looks tackier and less classy than The Times. </h6>

																		<p>But whilst you can see the difference, it takes a professional to understand what goes into making the difference. </p>

																		<p> Free fonts and clipart that have been downloaded from the internet are free for a reason: they don't have the same refinements that will give your invitations a polished, superior look.</p>

